No one can tell you exactly what’s causing this from a message alone. Three weeks of daily exhaustion despite 8 hours of sleep needs a medical evaluation.

Common causes include anemia/iron deficiency, thyroid problems, sleep apnea, depression/anxiety, infection, medication or alcohol effects, pregnancy, diabetes, and vitamin B12 deficiency.

What to do now:
- Schedule a primary care appointment this week.
- Ask for an exam and likely basic testing such as CBC, iron/ferritin, TSH, CMP, B12, glucose/A1c, and a pregnancy test if relevant.
- Review all meds, supplements, alcohol, cannabis, and other substances.
- If you snore, wake unrefreshed, or gasp in sleep, ask about sleep apnea.
- Don’t try to “push through” with heavy caffeine or intense exercise until you know why.

Get urgent care now if you also have chest pain, shortness of breath, fainting, black/bloody stools, fever, new weakness, confusion, severe depression, or thoughts of self-harm.No one can tell you exactly what’s causing this from a message alone. Three weeks of daily exhaustion despite 8 hours of sleep needs a medical evaluation.

